1
00:00:12,720 --> 00:00:13,880
Hurry up and blow on it for him.

2
00:00:13,880 --> 00:00:15,120
Or else it'll heal right up!

3
00:00:15,320 --> 00:00:16,880
Have some dignity, will you?

4
00:00:16,880 --> 00:00:18,160
There are still two people here!

5
00:00:21,400 --> 00:00:22,080
Let's go, let's go.

6
00:00:22,080 --> 00:00:22,760
Disgusting.

7
00:00:24,040 --> 00:00:24,880
Ignore them.

8
00:00:27,120 --> 00:00:27,960
Let's go, let's go.

9
00:00:28,120 --> 00:00:28,960
So disgusting.

10
00:00:29,680 --> 00:00:30,160
Show off your love,

11
00:00:30,160 --> 00:00:30,960
and you'll die fast.

12
00:00:31,800 --> 00:00:32,280
Wait a minute.

13
00:00:35,120 --> 00:00:36,040
Big Brother, what are you doing?

14
00:00:36,680 --> 00:00:37,480
I'm hurting myself.

15
00:00:37,480 --> 00:00:38,720
Aqin, blow on it for me!

16
00:00:39,120 --> 00:00:40,720
Aqin will blow on it when she visits your grave!

17
00:00:41,800 --> 00:00:42,320
How about the face?

18
00:00:42,440 --> 00:00:42,880
Don't.

19
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:43,840
You're so handsome.

20
00:00:43,840 --> 00:00:45,320
If you cut it, Aqin won't like you anymore.

21
00:00:45,320 --> 00:00:46,120
Then what should I do?

22
00:00:46,480 --> 00:00:47,480
Better stick to the hand.

23
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:50,400
Aqin!

24
00:00:51,480 --> 00:00:52,200
Aqin, I'm hurt!

25
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:53,200
Hurry and blow on it for me!

26
00:00:53,440 --> 00:00:54,080
Aqin!

27
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:55,760
Aqin!

28
00:00:56,440 --> 00:00:57,160
Aqin!

29
00:00:59,880 --> 00:01:00,680
Aqin!

30
00:01:03,440 --> 00:01:04,240
Miss Aqin!

31
00:01:04,440 --> 00:01:05,120
Miss Aqin!

32
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:06,400
My hand is cut too!

33
00:01:06,920 --> 00:01:07,760
Come over and take a look!

34
00:01:08,440 --> 00:01:09,240
Miss Aqin!

35
00:01:12,040 --> 00:01:13,120
If you don't look now, it'll heal!

36
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:42,920
Are all the guests here?

37
00:01:46,360 --> 00:01:47,840
Are all our friends here?

38
00:01:48,280 --> 00:01:49,080
Who is it?

39
00:01:51,680 --> 00:01:52,480
Village Chief.

40
00:01:52,480 --> 00:01:53,400
Xiaohua, you're here.

41
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:55,280
Is something the matter?

42
00:01:55,600 --> 00:01:57,120
We have some local specialties here.

43
00:01:57,360 --> 00:01:58,960
For our guests who came from afar.

44
00:01:58,960 --> 00:01:59,760
I brought them over.

45
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:03,400
No, no, you shouldn't have.

46
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:05,160
Why is this stuff so broken?

47
00:02:05,560 --> 00:02:06,080
Coincidence.

48
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:08,960
Breaking things brings peace!

49
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:11,480
Ever since you arrived,

50
00:02:11,640 --> 00:02:13,560
we haven't found a single whole thing in our village.

51
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:15,880
Look, Village Chief.

52
00:02:16,480 --> 00:02:17,520
If you have something to say, just say it.

53
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:18,680
Why bring these things?

54
00:02:19,440 --> 00:02:19,960
Well, we...

55
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:20,960
don't have any evidence either.

56
00:02:21,920 --> 00:02:22,960
So please, my lord,

57
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:24,520
take a look for yourself.

58
00:02:26,200 --> 00:02:26,920
It's nothing much.

59
00:02:26,920 --> 00:02:28,040
It's just that my wife

60
00:02:28,040 --> 00:02:29,480
has been entangled by a monster.

61
00:02:29,640 --> 00:02:30,440
A monster?

62
00:02:31,160 --> 00:02:32,320
E-Everyone, take a look.

63
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:39,880
I... I...

64
00:02:39,880 --> 00:02:40,800
Can I still be saved?

65
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:41,520
This...

66
00:02:41,920 --> 00:02:42,360
This... this...

67
00:02:42,720 --> 00:02:44,280
What is going on here?

68
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:45,880
Tell me, what are we supposed to do?

69
00:02:45,880 --> 00:02:46,760
Covered in monsters.

70
00:02:46,760 --> 00:02:48,360
Can't even go down to the fields to work now.

71
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:50,880
Our family only has this one laborer!

72
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:51,800
Wife.

73
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:53,240
I have to criticize you for this.

74
00:02:53,320 --> 00:02:54,360
Do you think all of this

75
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:55,920
was caused by our guests?

76
00:02:55,920 --> 00:02:56,600
Right?

77
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:58,280
It's just that we can't work this season.

78
00:02:58,520 --> 00:02:59,600
Will we starve in the winter?

79
00:02:59,920 --> 00:03:00,600
Worst case scenario,

80
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:01,560
we gnaw on tree bark,

81
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:02,680
dig up grass roots.

82
00:03:02,720 --> 00:03:03,240
Life...

83
00:03:03,440 --> 00:03:04,800
will go on.

84
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:05,720
Strategist.

85
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:08,120
They are hinting at us.

86
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:08,960
I know.

87
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:10,400
In the pond, we...

88
00:03:10,680 --> 00:03:11,440
the lotus roots we planted,

89
00:03:11,480 --> 00:03:12,160
the fish we raised,

90
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:14,120
have all been bitten like this by these monsters.

91
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:16,200
Tell me, what can be done?

92
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:18,880
How can you say such things in front of the guests?

93
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:20,240
The lotus roots died,

94
00:03:20,760 --> 00:03:22,040
we can plant them again.

95
00:03:22,080 --> 00:03:23,880
Won't they just die again if we replant?

96
00:03:23,880 --> 00:03:24,640
If they die,

97
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:25,760
so what?

98
00:03:26,200 --> 00:03:26,960
We...

99
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:28,080
are just like these lotus roots.

100
00:03:28,320 --> 00:03:29,040
If we die,

101
00:03:29,200 --> 00:03:30,360
so what?

102
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:32,320
Strategist,

103
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:34,040
this is definitely hinting at us.

104
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:36,880
Isn't the hint clear enough?

105
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:38,680
Folks,

106
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:40,760
who else wants to hint at us?

107
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:43,240
Mother,

108
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:44,800
don't be angry.

109
00:03:44,920 --> 00:03:46,320
Your son knows he was wrong.

110
00:03:47,080 --> 00:03:48,840
I've told you so many times,

111
00:03:49,160 --> 00:03:50,680
don't go swimming again next time.

112
00:03:50,840 --> 00:03:52,760
That pit is full of monsters.

113
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:54,080
But you just wouldn't listen.

114
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:54,800
Mother,

115
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:56,840
I wanted to catch fish for you to eat.

116
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:58,280
Your health is so poor,

117
00:03:58,280 --> 00:04:00,160
your son wanted to nourish you.

118
00:04:00,520 --> 00:04:02,120
My son has grown up.

119
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:04,160
It's Mother dragging you down. Mother...

120
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:06,320
Mother!

121
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:09,960
It's Mother's fault. Mother... Your son is useless.

122
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:10,640
My lord,

123
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:11,200
I...

124
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:11,720
Daqiang,

125
00:04:12,440 --> 00:04:13,240
that's enough.

126
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:15,360
Hinting like this is enough.

127
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:17,720
If the acting goes too far, I won't be able to play along.

128
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:19,040
Village Chief,

129
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:20,640
let's just speak plainly.

130
00:04:20,640 --> 00:04:21,400
Okay?

131
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:24,320
Actually, we...

132
00:04:24,520 --> 00:04:25,520
just want to ask you, Sir,

133
00:04:25,520 --> 00:04:26,560
if you have a good solution.

134
00:04:27,560 --> 00:04:28,840
Ever since that big vat of yours

135
00:04:28,920 --> 00:04:30,080
fell into the pond,

136
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:32,360
these things have been happening.

137
00:04:33,080 --> 00:04:33,800
Vat?

138
00:04:35,680 --> 00:04:37,080
Then let's go take a look immediately.

139
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:38,200
Okay, okay.

140
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:39,120
Let's go, let's go.

141
00:04:39,440 --> 00:04:40,600
Strategist, this...

142
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:41,640
Let's go have a look.

143
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:43,240
Let's look together.

144
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:45,480
You two,

145
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:46,840
these monsters all

146
00:04:46,840 --> 00:04:48,200
ran here from the fields.

147
00:04:48,440 --> 00:04:49,160
Look,

148
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:50,600
they are all over the place.

149
00:04:58,600 --> 00:05:00,040
It's the one.

150
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:02,040
What a coincidence.

151
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:04,000
Could this thing...

152
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:06,080
...be the one from the jar our Lord bestowed...

153
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:07,400
...the Silt-Clearing Marvel?

154
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:10,040
How does this thing clear silt?

155
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:11,160
Come look.

156
00:05:12,080 --> 00:05:14,120
It's good at burrowing in mud.

157
00:05:14,360 --> 00:05:16,600
Maybe it really can clear silt.

158
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:22,400
This is the legendary Silt-Clearing Marvel.

159
00:05:23,360 --> 00:05:24,520
Silt-Clearing Marvel.

160
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:33,200
Isn't this the brother who came down the mountain for food?

161
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:34,840
Don't fight.

162
00:05:36,840 --> 00:05:37,280
Right.

163
00:05:37,280 --> 00:05:38,440
Fighting isn't allowed in the village.

164
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:45,400
Do you need this?

165
00:05:46,520 --> 00:05:48,080
If you need it, just tell us.

166
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:49,240
It's not like we wouldn't give it to you.

167
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:49,840
Look.

168
00:05:49,960 --> 00:05:51,160
There's plenty here.

169
00:05:51,280 --> 00:05:52,120
You want it?

170
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:53,200
Come get it anytime.

171
00:05:53,840 --> 00:05:54,480
From now on,

172
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:55,680
you have to be careful.

173
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:57,480
Stop doing such dangerous things.

174
00:05:57,680 --> 00:05:59,400
You almost fell into the river just now.

175
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:01,480
Tell us if you need anything.

176
00:06:01,480 --> 00:06:02,320
You know?

177
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:05,560
Don't live on the mountain anymore.

178
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:07,840
Look at the state you're in.

179
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:10,080
It'd be bad if word got out.

180
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:12,520
People might think our village mistreats guests.

181
00:06:22,280 --> 00:06:23,080
Here.

182
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:28,560
Who told you to laugh?

183
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:30,160
Wipe that smile off.

184
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:33,160
Alright, alright.

185
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:35,040
Go.

186
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:36,040
Call your big brother here.

187
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:37,160
Aqin is missing.

188
00:06:37,160 --> 00:06:38,200
Big Brother went to find Aqin.

189
00:06:40,840 --> 00:06:41,720
Aqin.

190
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:43,880
Aqin.

191
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:46,840
Aqin.

192
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:58,440
Aqin.

193
00:07:08,840 --> 00:07:09,640
Aqin.

194
00:07:10,760 --> 00:07:11,640
Brother Wei.

195
00:07:12,760 --> 00:07:14,200
Go, bring General Wei here.

196
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:15,000
On it, Sister Aqin.

197
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:24,960
Aqin.

198
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:26,280
Aqin.

199
00:07:26,280 --> 00:07:26,800
General Wei.

200
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:27,440
General Wei.

201
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:30,640
Don't attack.

202
00:07:30,640 --> 00:07:31,360
We're on the same side.

203
00:07:31,640 --> 00:07:32,440
We're on the same side.

204
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:33,800
You spy from Daye Kingdom.

205
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:34,600
Who's on the same side as you?

206
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:37,000
Brother-in-law, stop it.

207
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:39,680
Brother-in-law.

208
00:07:39,960 --> 00:07:41,360
I don't know any sister of yours.

209
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:42,200
It's Sister Aqin.

210
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:43,280
She sent me to pick you up.

211
00:07:43,280 --> 00:07:44,400
She even prepared rich broth for you.

212
00:07:44,760 --> 00:07:45,560
Aqin.

213
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:46,840
Yes, General Wei.

214
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:48,560
We'll be family from now on.

215
00:07:48,760 --> 00:07:50,120
Please look after us.

216
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:52,200
I need to ask Aqin.

217
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:53,040
Lead the way.

218
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:00,840
Brother Wei.

219
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:02,280
Come taste the soup I made.

220
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:03,640
I simmered it all night.

221
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:09,560
It's delicious.

222
00:08:09,880 --> 00:08:12,040
When I trained in the mountains with my master,

223
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:13,200
I often cooked game.

224
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:13,920
Taste it.

225
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:25,400
Is it good?

226
00:08:27,920 --> 00:08:28,840
Your identity.

227
00:08:28,840 --> 00:08:29,760
Who else knows?

228
00:08:30,840 --> 00:08:31,640
Identity.

229
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:33,040
What identity?

230
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:33,760
What identity?

231
00:08:33,760 --> 00:08:34,400
What identity are you talking about?

232
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:35,560
Your identity...

233
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:38,560
Everyone knows.

234
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:40,040
The people in the village,

235
00:08:40,040 --> 00:08:40,920
my friends,

236
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,120
and my master.

237
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:44,400
So many people.

238
00:08:44,760 --> 00:08:45,800
How am I supposed to kill them all?
